The paper presents a model-agnostic approach to identifying important features in learned models, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The approach is evaluated on biomedical applications, indicating a focus on applications of machine learning in the life sciences. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
